{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"GAP CONFIRMED LIVE + FIX AUTHORED. Empirical proof (AC2 evidence, inverted): pushed change 198 to refs/for/refs/heads/feature/s3-ci on the running Gerrit 3.14.1. Result: LLM-Review+1 (bot is branch-agnostic, cast normally) but Verified=none and NO 'STARTED' CI message ever appeared -> g2p's workflow_dispatch(ref=refs/heads/feature/s3-ci) targeted a ref absent from the GitHub mirror -> 422/no-op -> no CI run. This is the design-assumption failure S3 exists to catch, now proven.\n\nFIX (authored): infra/gerrit/replication.config now adds 'push = refs/heads/feature/*:refs/heads/feature/*' to [remote github], scoped to feature/* (not a wildcard, never refs/meta/*), so the dispatch ref resolves and CI runs. Documented tradeoff: feature branches become transiently visible on the GitHub mirror (deleted after merge-back; mirror=false means Gerrit-side deletion won't auto-prune GitHub — S6 inventory + merge-back cleanup handle teardown).\n\nDEPLOYMENT BLOCKER: applying this fix to the running Gerrit requires (per setup-replication.sh) SSH to the EC2 host + copying to /var/gerrit/site/etc/replication.config + a Gerrit RESTART (remote plugin reload is disabled). My AWS session is EXPIRED and I have no host SSH key, so I cannot deploy it or run a Gerrit restart. Consequently AC2-AC5 (live run-log evidence that feature/* + merge changes get Verified) are BLOCKED on operator deployment of this fix. AC1 (verified g2p branch-filtering statement) is complete via source investigation + the live gap proof."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783061422728231001,"uuid":"ddb2f20e-8af8-46ad-9c09-7ea79b1f20bf"}